<plot>This short promotes the premise that movies often create a demand for the fashions seen in them. It starts with a short vignette in rural America. A mother and daughter go to town to buy a new dress. In the dress shop window is a designer dress worn by 'Joan Crawford' (qv) in a recent movie. We then go to Hollywood and visit 'Adrian (I)' (qv), MGM's chief of costume design, and see how multiple copies of a single clothing pattern are produced. The film ends with short segments of several MGM features.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?243569</url></doc>
